# Project rules (entry)

Use **`@`-references** instead of pasting long excerpts. Modular sources:

| Concern | Open |
|--------|------|
| Frozen UI / API vs safe refactors | `@.ai/core/refactor-policy.md` |
| Engineering habits | `@.ai/core/rules.md` |
| Product + sidebar + stack | `@.ai/projects/merchant-dashboard.md` |
| Visual system summary | `@design-guidelines/OVERVIEW.md` |
| Spec index (`rules/**/*.mdc`) | `@design-guidelines/INDEX.md` |
| Pack handoff / new repo | `@design-guidelines/README.md` |
| Design stub (legacy links) | `@.ai/projects/ump-design-guidelines.md` |
| Module patterns (Agent Skill) | `@.cursor/skills/build-dashboard-module/SKILL.md` |
| Subagents (delegated specialists) | `.cursor/agents/*.md` — index `@.cursor/agents/README.md`, reference `@.cursor/docs/subagents.md` |
| Prompts | `@.ai/prompts/safe-restructure.md`, `@.ai/prompts/concept-guidelines.md` |

**Guards:** Instruction-only work → do **not** edit `src/`. Granular design rules do **not** override `@.ai/core/refactor-policy.md`.

**Scoped UI rule:** `.cursor/rules/design-guidelines.mdc` (applies when `src/app` or `design-guidelines` files are in context).

Rule types, globs, and `AGENTS.md`: [cursor.com/docs/rules](https://cursor.com/docs/rules). **Agent Skills** (this repo: `.cursor/skills/`): [cursor.com/docs/skills](https://cursor.com/docs/skills). **Subagents** (this repo: `.cursor/agents/`): [cursor.com/docs/subagents](https://cursor.com/docs/subagents).
